Common.LocationDescription.Common.Text:
The property is located just two blocks from Interstate-24 exit 47. The
property is highly-visible and located directly across the street from TopGolf at
the signalized intersection of Spring (Jefferson) Street and Cowan Street.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
The property previously functioned as an auto mechanic facility and is best
suited for complete redevelopment.

ZONING OVERVIEW
The subject property is located within multiple zoning overlays, all of which
permit a broad range of uses. The property is also located in an opportunity
zone.
• Mixed-Use Intensive Overlay
• Urban Zoning Overlay
• River North Urban Design Overlay. This zoning overlay encourages density
and permits a range of future uses which include:
• Office
• Residential
• Hotel
• Retail/Restaurant
• Civic Space
• Public Use Areas and Greenways
• Zoning Designation: MUI-A (Mixed-Use Intensive)
• Overlay - Flood Plain

The EMP District is intended to accommodate office, light manufacturing, research and development, warehousing,
wholesale, processing and commercial uses in order to promote economic viability, encourage employment growth, and limit

relatively clean and quiet manner, and should not be obnoxious to nearby residential or commercial uses.
